    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "#(1). Bagging\n",
        "\n",
        "**Bagging (Bootstrap Aggregating) is an ensemble learning method that combines\n",
        "multiple base learners by training them on\n",
        "different subsets of the training data using bootstrapping.\n",
        "Each base learner is trained independently,\n",
        "and their predictions are combined to make the final prediction.**\n",
        "\n",
        "#(1). Bagging Process:\n",
        "\n",
        "(a). Data Sampling: Bagging starts by creating multiple random subsets (samples) of the training data using bootstrapping.\n",
        "Bootstrapping involves sampling the training data with replacement, which means that each subset can\n",
        "contain duplicate instances and may not include all instances.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "(b). Base Learner Training: Each subset is used to train a separate base leamer independently.\n",
        "The base learners can be any model capable of making predictions, such as decision trees, support vector machines,\n",
        "or neural networks. Each base learner is trained on its respective subset of the data\n",
        "\n",
        "(c). Prediction Aggregation: Once the base leamers are trained, their predictions are combined to make the final prediction.\n",
        "For classification problems, the most common aggregation method is voting, where the majority vote among the base\n",
        "learners' predictions determines the final prediction. For regression problems, the predictions are typically averaged."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "uJnzrif5GUbn"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 2,
